The paper discusses approval-based multiwinner voting rules, which are a topic in Computational Social Choice (cs.GT). The paper also proposes new noise models specifically tailored for approval votes and committees, which could fall under Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) or Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves analyzing and evaluating the effectiveness of these voting rules, which could fall under Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) or Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
